The paper deals with efficient and accurate classification of PolSAR images using deep learning techniques. Specifically, it proposes a novel pixel-refining parallel mapping network in the complex domain for PolSAR image classification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning algorithms and training techniques, which are commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves the use of contextual semantic features, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
